Europe
------
[1] Ukraine
Date: Wed 7 Dec 2011
Source: Forum [edited]
http://en.for-ua.com/news/2011/12/07/160058.html


Six-fold increase in measles cases
----------------------------------
The Ministry of Health has recorded an increase in the number of
measles cases in the Lviv, Ivano-Frankivsk, Zakarpattia and Rivne
regions, according to deputy health minister Raisa Moiseenko. She
explains this increase as due both to the rising incidence of measles
throughout Europe, and to the fact that in 2008 Ukraine was unable to
conduct a large-scale campaign of immunization of adolescents and
young people against the disease.

Deputy minister Moiseenko said in comparison with the previous year,
measles incidence has increased six-fold, and the number of cases as
of October [2011] was 193. In the summer the Health Ministry had
discounted the threat of a measles epidemic in Ukraine.

